data.shownotes: This is King Gizzard's first US show and was released through the Official Bootlegger program as Live at Levitation ‘14. The lyrics to I'm in Your Mind and Am I in Heaven? contained alternate or incomplete lyrics compared to the album versions which came out almost 6-months after this performance.

I’m In Your Mind contained alternate lyrics. Before The Wholly Ghost, Stu asks Joey if they should play Angel next which was the working title for Her and I (Slow Jam 2) and Joey says they should play Ghost instead the working title for The Wholly Ghost. Before Her and I, Stu asks the crowd "Do you mind if we play a chilled out jammy one or is that boring?".  This is the earliest recording available for the song, which strongly resembles the studio version, although they are still working out the jam sections.  After, Stu asks if they can keep playing new stuff because "they need practice".  Following Am I in Heaven?, Stu shouts out the opener, Ice Balloons, and gives them a "big extra thank you" for letting them borrow their equipment.

KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist may be incomplete. Robot Stop, Muckraker and The River were confirmed by audio/video and the rest were reported by attendees. Although the band claimed on 2022-06-17 that they first debuted Robot Stop at Bonnaroo on 2015-06-12, the brief audio/video clip of Robot Stop from this performance appears to contradict this. We have chosen to include the song on the setlist despite the band's claim as additional audio/video evidence shows that the band were recording and rehearsing songs for Nonagon Infinity as early as February 2015, as well as Evil Death Roll and Gamma Knife being debuted during the other Gizzfest shows. There is also uncertainty as to whether all new songs have been properly identified, if the songs are in the correct order, and if a complete Head On/Pill was played or only the Pill section. If anyone has any additional information about this show or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

High Voltage (AC/DC) played before and as the band walked on stage for the first set. All Is Known was introduced as a new song and contained alternate lyrics. During Billabong Valley, the guitar strap fell off the Flying Microtonal Banana while Ambrose was using it, with Joey jokingly telling Stu afterwards that his guitar was broken and that Ambrose should "stick to the blues harp". NOBODY'S BABY (Sheer Mag) played before and as the band walked on stage for the second set. Before Gamma Knife, the crowd started chanting for Stu to do a "shoey", to which he told them to "be reasonable" and that he was "too old for that". The Balrog was introduced as a new song. Am I In Heaven? contained a medley of teases and quotes including Alter Me, Cellophane, Rattlesnake, Hot Water, Head On/Pill and The River as well as a Sea of Trees jam with lyrics. This performance was filmed in 360-degree video and released as "King Gizzard & The Lizard Wizard - 360° Full Concert" on the Banalarama YouTube channel, featuring audio mixed by Stu
Webcast live by Pitchfork. Night one was performed in the grand ballroom.
Sea Of Trees was played for the first time known since 2014-10-24. (217 show gap)

This show featured the debut of Vomit Coffin. Following Rattlesnake, the band wished a happy birthday to Eric. Am I In Heaven? contained teases and quotes of Cellophane, The River, Head On/Pill, I'm In Your Mind, Sea of Trees, Rattlesnake, and Robot Stop. Prior to the show, Stu accidentally posted a link containing demos for all of Polygondwanaland to the Facebook fan page under the name “Blinky Bill”. Although removed shortly after, someone was able to download the first two demos causing Stu to message them claiming he was a fan named Han-Tyumi and asked for the demos not to be reposted. If anyone has any additional information on what was played at this show or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.
During final song Stu crowd surfed out of the venue and into the sea, while the band continued to play.
Performed at the William's Green stage.

data.showtitle: Infest the Rat's Nest Album Release Show
data.shownotes:
“Infest the Rats’ Nest” album was released the day of the show. Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before and as the band went on stage. Open Water featured a drum solo. Am I In Heaven? contained Alter Me, Robot Stop and Cellophane teases and quotes and Rattlesnake and Big Fig Wasp teases.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 100

Evil Star was played through the PA speakers as the band went on stage. Open Water featured a drum solo. Joey dedicated Work This Time, which contained a guitar solo, to Dan Bilzerian, with him claiming he saw "about 500 Dan Bilzerians" before the show. After Doom City, Ambrose thanked openers ORB and Stonefield. Before Cyboogie, the Han-Tyumi voice was used to say "Hello" repeatedly. Gamma Knife contained Robot Stop teases and quotes. Am I In Heaven? contained Boogieman Sam, Cyboogie and Alter Me quotes and teases and Rattlesnake, Hot Water and Head On/Pill teases. 

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 100

Tezeta and Venusian 2 were on the written setlist but not played. Planet B was not on the written setlist. data.jamchart_notes: Features Stu on flute with a typical Pill flute jam, but also contains a rare Hot Water jam with flute.
data.shownotes:
Evil Star was played through the PA speakers as the band went on stage. Cut Throat Boogie contained a Cruel Millennial outro. Wah Wah contained a River intro as well as The River teases and quotes. During the River intro of Wah Wah an audience member got on stage, who Joey then passed his microphone to before security escorted them offstage. Am I In Heaven? contained Robot Stop, Head On/Pill, Cellophane and I'm In Your Mind quotes and teases, Boogieman Sam and Hot Wax quotes and Hot Water teases, as well as featuring Stu on vocoder and later flute for an extended Hot Water jam which was followed by Cavs crowd surfing while Stu played drums. Let Me Mend the Past and Wah Wah from this show are featured in the Chunky Shrapnel album.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 100

Rattlesnake was introduced by Joey as “the most annoying song ever written”. After Am I In Heaven Joey said “We’re King Gizzard and the Lizard Wizard which is the stupidest name for a band”. Am I In Heaven contained Rattlesnake and Alter Me quotes and teases and Boogieman Sam teases. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Rattlesnake, Cyboogie and Am I In Heaven? were confirmed by an audience recording. The remaining songs were confirmed via contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This was the Jams Night show of the Princess Theatre residency, the second of five planned shows, each featuring a different specific genre and preannounced songs. Am I in Heaven? contained Rattlesnake teases, Head On/Pill teases/quotes and Boogieman Sam quotes. Sea of Trees contained Hot Water teases and a jam which featured Stu playing the flute. Head On/Pill contained Am I in Heaven? and Hot Water teases and quotes. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings exist. Recordings of Sleep Drifter and Straws in the Wind are unavailable and most other songs are incomplete. The missing songs were confirmed based on the preannounced song lists for each of the 5 planned genre specific shows and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea Edition of 200

data.showtitle: Return of the Curse of Timeland
data.shownotes: This show was billed as Return of the Curse of Timeland (a rescheduling of their cancelled 2021 New Year's Eve Timeland Festival) and featured the debuts of Magenta Mountain, The Garden Goblin, The Dripping Tap, and Soy-Protein Munt Machine. Timeland was played over the PA as the pre-show music. A model of London’s Big Ben clock tower, approximately 20 ft (6 m) tall, with the words “Time is Ephemeral” and “Music is Ephemeral” written on the clock’s face was erected in the back right corner of the stage.  The clock hands ran forward at an accelerated pace throughout the show.  Am I in Heaven? contained Rattlesnake teases and Boogieman Sam quotes/teases. Evil Death Roll contained Robot Stop teases. Trapdoor was played for the first time known since 2016-09-09. (259 show gap) The Dripping Tap was introduced as a song about a tap that won’t stop dripping.  Smoke & Mirrors was played over the PA as the setbreak music. Hot Wax was played for the first time since 2018-06-20. (114 show gap) Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs. Rattlesnake contained Boogieman Sam quotes and featured another Cavs drum solo, during which the band destroyed the clock tower presiding over the stage and passed out the pieces into the crowd. The on-stage carnage appears to have extended to some of the band’s equipment, as the final portion of Rattlesnake was performed with Joey playing the FMB and Stu singing with no instrument.
data.opener: Babe Rainbow, Stonefield, Ajak Kwai, Nice Biscuit, Bones & Jones w/Folk BItch Trio

data.shownotes: The show began with a chant of “fuck shit up” by the crowd, which was repeated several times throughout the show. Self-Immolate was introduced as a song about setting yourself on fire. Before starting Magenta Mountain the crowd’s chant was changed to “ma-gen-ta.” Slow Jam 1 contained Iron Lung quotes. Supreme Ascendancy was introduced as a song about “how much Amby loves our lord and savior…Satan!” SPELLLING and The Chats were shouted out after Oddlife. Following Ontology Stu and the audience had a discussion of the apple that Stu was eating during the show. The Lord of Lightning contained a Cellophane tease. Before Dead-Beat, Stu announced that they would be playing an older song. This announcement prompted several requests from the audience, including God is in the Rhythm, “Taste of an Orange” (Almacknjack) and “Stairway to Heaven” (Led Zeppelin) which was then teased by Joey, who then claimed that he had no idea how to play that song and referred to it as Stairway to Kevin. Am I in Heaven? contained Her and I (Slow Jam 2) teases, God Is Calling Me Back Home teases, The Dripping Tap teases/quotes, Boogieman Sam teases/quotes, Rattlesnake teases, Hot Wax quotes and Head On/Pill teases/quotes. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Special shout out to our very own @spidzzle for the recording located on Archive.org!
data.venuename: Event Lawn at Virgin Hotels Las Vegas

data.shownotes: Head On/Pill featured Ambrose on sax and Stu playing flute, as well as Hot Water and The Dripping Tap teases and Iron Lung quotes. Rattlesnake contained Doom City teases and O.N.E. and Automation teases and quotes. Am I In Heaven? contained Head On/Pill and The Dripping Tap teases and quotes, as well as The Grim Reaper quotes. During Am I In Heaven?, a cake and flowers was brought out for Cookie's birthday, and both were thrown into the crowd soon after. Self-Immolate and Organ Farmer were on the written setlist after Rattlesnake but were cut. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Head On/Pill, The Garden Goblin, Rattlesnake, and Am I In Heaven? have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via the physical written setlist and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

Superbug (lyric changed from “H1N1” to “Coronavirus” referencing COVID-19). Inner Cell was dedicated to the former Australian Prime Minister Scott Morrison, who had lost an election that day. Inner Cell was played for the first time since 2019-10-15 (54 show gap), and Loyalty and Horology were played for the first time since 2019-10-18 (52 show gap). Cut Throat Boogie featured Boogieman Sam teases and quotes, Change teases, “Got My Mojo Working” (Ann Cole) quotes, and “My Babe” (Little Walter) quotes. Persistence featured Change teases and Horology teases. Am I in Heaven? featured Cut Throat Boogie, Hot Water, and Change teases and The Dripping Tap, Iron Lung, Cellophane, Persistence, Sea of Trees, Magenta Mountain, and Ice V teases and quotes. The Lord of Lightning was on the printed setlist after Magenta Mountain but was not played.
data.soundcheck: (possibly incomplete) Inner Cell, Loyalty, Magenta Mountain, Mars for the Rich

data.shownotes: Fourth of five nights in Barcelona for Primavera Sound. Am I In Heaven? contained Sadie Sorceress quotes and Hot Water teases. The intro to Nuclear Fusion was done by the entire band around one mic. 'Float Along - Fill Your Lungs' was listed on the printed setlist but not played. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Straws In The Wind, Nuclear Fusion, Sadie Sorceress, and Boogieman Sam have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

data.jamchart_notes: Only a partial video available, but worth watching for both a Dripping Tap jam and a Hypertension jam inside, both with lyrics, as well as Alter Me and Crumbling Castle high energy teases and quotes.
data.shownotes: Rattlesnake contained Automation and O.N.E. teases. Am I In Heaven? contained Magenta Mountain and Head On/Pill teases, Alter Me and Crumbling Castle teases and quotes, and both a Dripping Tap and Hypertension jam with lyrics. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Hot Water, Magenta Mountain, and most of Am I In Heaven? have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via the physical written setlist for the night and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete or incorrect. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

This show featured the debut of Ice V. Wah Wah began with the intro to The River, and subsequently contained Crumbling Castle and The River teases. Ambrose quoted It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) before Doom City. O.N.E. began with the intro to Straws in the Wind instead of the customary intro. Pleura contained a quote of “Freedom” (Rage Against the Machine). Straws in the Wind was dedicated to Russell Brand. Smoke and Mirrors was played over the PA as the setbreak music. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo. Ambergris contained an Ice V tease. Before The Reticent Raconteur, Leah Senior was introduced to the stage as “The Original Balrog” and Joey gave a shoutout to her live bass player Jack [Robbins], with the bonus trivia that he was also in Stu’s first band Almacknjack. The Reticent Raconteur was played for the first time since 2021-02-24 (61 show gap). The Reticent Raconteur and The Lord of Lightning featured narration by Leah Senior. The Fourth Colour was played for the first time since 2019-11-23 (70 show gap). Am I in Heaven? contained The Dripping Tap teases. Poster by Jason Galea 800 standard / 50 Foil Print

Vomit Coffin featured the now-infamous “Amby Snot Rocket”. Blame It on the Weather was humorously announced as the “complete opposite style of music” to the show-opening Murder of the Universe suite. Work This Time featured a guitar solo. Cut Throat Boogie was announced as a song about Ambrose getting stabbed in the neck with a broken bottle. Wah Wah began with the intro to The River and subsequently featured The River quotes and teases, as well as a jam. Sadie Sorceress featured an additional verse from The Grim Reaper played over the music to Sadie Sorceress. Joey requested the cameraperson zoom in to his face as close as possible during the intro to Self-Immolate and introduced Cavs as “John Henry Bonham”, followed by a drum solo and a “Moby Dick” (Led Zeppelin) tease, plus an additional brief drum solo and “Moby Dick” tease at the end of the song. Before Her and I (Slow Jam 2), the weather was discussed and the band’s ignorance regarding Fahrenheit to Celsius conversions was revealed. The song itself featured a Flamethrower jam, Slow Jam 1 and Magma teases, and a brief Cut Throat Boogie jam. Hot Wax was dedicated to one of the band's sound engineers, Joe Santarpia. Timeland was played over the PA as the setbreak music. Head On/Pill opened with “The Star-Spangled Banner” intro, contained Hypertension teases and a Witchcraft tease, and was unfinished leading into Am I in Heaven?. Venusian 1 closed with a Cavs drum solo which led into Venusian 2. Ambrose introduced Billabong Valley as being about a bushranger and is interrupted by Joey calling him “mad-cunt Morgan”. Let Me Mend The Past, which contained an It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) quote, was announced as a song about Ambrose’s somewhat troubled upbringing and was dedicated to Edith, Ambrose’s sister. Alter Me III and Altered Beast IV were performed with Leah Senior providing the narration. Float Along - Fill Your Lungs contained a metal jam. Tetrachromacy and Hypertension were on the printed setlist but cut due to time constraints. This show was released through the Official Bootlegger program as part of Live at Red Rocks ‘22. Poster By Jason Galea Second Edition of Poster

This show was part of the 2022 Rhythm & Alps Festival. “The End” (The Doors) was briefly quoted after The Fourth Colour. Am I In Heaven? contained Witchcraft, Head On/Pill and The Dripping Tap teases. Amusing banter followed Am I in Heaven? where the band talked about their New Year’s resolutions. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo, during which Stu and Joey sprayed the crowd with champagne, followed by a full band “Moby Dick” (Led Zeppelin) tease. Boogieman Sam contained “My Babe” (Little Walter) and “Going Up the Country” (Canned Heat) quotes. Some other artists appearing at this festival were specifically shouted out by Joey: Marlon Williams, Sampa the Great, and Dope Lemon.

This show featured the debut of Gila Monster. Honey contained Billabong Valley, Automation, and Rattlesnake teases. Iron Lung contained Hypertension teases. The River contained Wah Wah teases. Self-Immolate contained a “Fire” (Jimi Hendrix) quote and featured a drum solo by Cavs with “Machine Gun” (Jimi Hendrix) teases. After an instrumental intro to Am I in Heaven?, Stu, Joey, and Amby discuss recent dreams before continuing with the song. The song itself contained a “Stairway to Heaven” (Led Zeppelin) quote as well as “Stiff Upper Lip” (AC/DC) and Rattlesnake teases. Poster By Drew Millward

The Wheel was played for the first time since Dec. 19, 2021 (94 show gap). Alter Me III contained Witchcraft teases. Altered Beast IV contained Converge teases. Sadie Sorceress was dedicated to Ambrose's 99-year-old grandmother and contained an extra verse from The Grim Reaper and quotes of Torture Chamber. Am I In Heaven? contained “animals in Australia” lyrics, Witchcraft teases, Head On/Pill teases, Ice V teases, Hot Water teases, Shanghai teases, The Dripping Tap teases, I Am Not a Man Unless I Have a Woman quotes and Sea of Trees teases. Poster By Jason Galea 100 Standard / 30 Foil

Rattlesnake contained Honey teases and Sleep Drifter teases/quotes. Honey contained Rattlesnake teases and Sleep Drifter teases. Shanghai featured a Grow Wings and Fly “let’s get real high” jam. Stu teased “Voodoo Child (Slight Return)” (Jimi Hendrix) during the leadup to Invisible Face. Invisible Face was played for the first time since June 6, 2017 (313 show gap) and was performed in full for the first time. Wah Wah contained The River teases. Ice V contained "Ain’t It Funky Now" (James Brown) teases. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs, during which Amby burned his copy of the setlist. This show was released through the Official Bootlegger program as part of Live in Chicago '23. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Invisible Face appears in setlists 40 times prior to this show. Of these, 29 have no recording available and one recording cuts off before the end of the song. The remaining 10 are all complete recordings of unfinished versions in which only the first two verses are performed. Based on these facts and the comments made by the band at this show, KGLW.net staff believe that the unavailable versions were also unfinished and that this is the first complete performance of Invisible Face. If anyone has conclusive evidence to the contrary, please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea 460 Standard / 130 Foil

This show featured the debut of Dragon. Am I In Heaven? contained teases of Hot Water and Witchcraft.

Poster By Elora Sperber

This show was cut short due to heavy winds at the festival site. The band (except Cavs) wore pilot uniforms for the full show. Prior to Gaia, Amby did a vocal tease of “Tequila” (The Champs). Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs which led into a Motor Spirit jam. During Mars For The Rich a confetti cannon went off prompting Stu to sing "What the fuck is happening?" Am I In Heaven? contained Supreme Ascendancy quotes. The Grim Reaper contained "Intergalactic” (Beastie Boys) quotes and an appearance on stage by a dancing People-Vulture. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Gaia through The Grim Reaper have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via the written setlist for the show and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This was King Gizzard's first show in South America. Head On/Pill contained Robot Stop teases and Am I In Heaven? teases & quotes.  Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases & quotes.  Venusian 2 contained Converge quotes.

This show featured the debut of Flamethrower. Joey commented after, that they would do the last half of the song next time. Am I In Heaven? contained Sad Pilot, Flamethrower, and Cut Throat Boogie teases, a Witchcraft tease, and Iron Lung teases and quotes. Following Flamethrower, Joey shouted out opener Grace Cummings. This Thing contained La Grange (ZZ Top) teases and lyrics parodying the song. Iron Lung contained a Hypertension tease. Hypertension contained Witchcraft, Magma, and Ice V teases. Work This Time contained Ice V teases from Cavs. Float Along - Fill Your Lungs contained a metal jam. The written setlist had Doom City and Minimum Brain Size before Float Along - Fill Your Lungs but they were cut for time. Poster by Amy Jean; Edition of 100

Hot Water contained Robot Stop, Am I In Heaven?, and The Dripping Tap teases. Robot Stop, which was incomplete, contained Ice V, Daily Blues, and Am I In Heaven? teases and Field of Vision quotes. The second Hot Water contained a chant of "New York City". Ice V contained a "Blindness" (The Fall) jam and improvised lyrics. The Bitter Boogie contained the drums from Muddy Water and Ice V teases. You Can Be Your Silhouette was introduced as a song about being who you want to be. Hot Wax contained You Can Be Your Silhouette teases. Converge was introduced as a song about storms before Planet B, as Stu confused them on the setlist. The Great Chain of Being contained an "On The Road Again" (Canned Heat) tease. Motor Spirit was dedicated to Cavs "because it's about cars" and contained a You Can Be Your Silhouette and Robot Stop tease. Slow Jam 1 contained Crumbling Castle, Sad Pilot and Ice V teases. Billabong Valley was preceded by a "Microtonal Jazz Jam" with Stu referencing Sexy Alien and Joey singing The Star Spangled Banner. In the song itself, Ambrose crowdsurfed on an inflatable gator and quoted Should I Stay Or Should I Go (The Clash). Following Automation, Joey shouted out opener Geese. A crowd member then told the band to play Fishing For Fishies and the full band (besides Cavs) teased it. The band then started to name classic rock songs and teased Stairway To Heaven and Moby Dick (both Led Zeppelin), and Smoke On the Water (Deep Purple). Stu also shouted out Australian band Cold Chisel. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg contained a Hypertension tease. Am I In Heaven? contained Evil Death Roll, and Converge teases and Hot Water teases and quotes. Sad Pilot was on the printed setlist but was skipped.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition of 1200
Holographic Edition of 300

Audience member Joe did the vocal intro to Nuclear Fusion. Cellophane contained I'm In Your Mind, Am I In Heaven?, and Lord of Lightning teases. Mystery Jack was last played 2022-05-31. (138 show gap) Hypertension contained Witchcraft and Hot Water teases. Ambrose did a short breakdance after his verse of Le Risque and said Raygun taught him everything he knows. The Grim Reaper contained Telescope (Ambrose Kenny-Smith & GUM), Torture Chamber, Body Movin' and Intergalactic (Beastie Boys) quotes. Magenta Mountain was attempted but only a jam was played (Titled We're Doin' It Together on the Official Bootleg) because Joey's synth wasn't working. This Thing contained a The Land Before Timeland tease. The intro to Am I In Heaven? (which was not on the printed setlist) contained Lava and The Dripping Tap teases and the song itself contained a This Thing tease and a Hypertension jam with lyrics. 

Poster By Job van Rijen
Standard: 600
Gold Foil: 200

data.jamchart_notes: heaven got that almost metal-y jam -> calm space -> mind fuzz part
data.shownotes:
This show featured the debut of Hog Calling Contest. The first The Bitter Boogie contained the drums from Muddy Water and Muddy Water teases. Muddy Water contained the drums from The Bitter Boogie and The Bitter Boogie teases. The Bitter Boogie Reprise also contained a Muddy Water tease. Elbow was last played 2018-11-23. (257 show gap) After The River, which contained a Lost Woods (Koji Kondo) tease, the band wished Jay Weinberg a happy birthday. Le Risque and Gila Monster featured Jay Weinberg on drums. During Le Risque, Cavs went into the audience for his vocal part and asked an audience member (Devin) to do the "Let's Ride" lyric. Stressin’ was last played 2022-06-01. (141 show gap) Chang'e contained Witchcraft quotes. Extinction contained Gondii quotes.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard - 1000
Gold Foil - 300

Slow Jam 1 contained Crumbling Castle and Am I In Heaven? teases. This Thing contained Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes. Am I In Heaven? contained The Land Before Timeland, Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) and Witchcraft teases and a Slow Jam 1 jam with lyrics, and featured improvised alternate lyrics. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs. Nuclear Fusion featured community taper Mystery Jack for the vocal intro. Hog Calling Contest was teased prior to Antarctica, which contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Boogieman Sam contained La Grange (ZZ Top) teases and a Riff Raff (AC/DC) jam. Following Boogieman Sam, Joey mentioned that the band would be performing at the Hollywood Bowl with the L.A. Philharmonic on their upcoming tour in 2025, which was previously unannounced at the time. Texas Flood and Pride and Joy (Stevie Ray Vaughan) were teased prior to Daily Blues, which contained Hot Water teases. Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases, This Thing quotes, Forty Six and 2 (Tool) teases and Master of the Universe (Hawkwind) teases and quotes. Gamma Knife was unfinished. Ice V contained The Lord of Lightning teases. The Lord of Lightning contained Cellophane teases. Le Risque featured Jay Weinberg on drums. Additionally, Cavs got an audience member to perform a laugh for the song and brought Jay's wife Chloe on stage to perform the 'Let's Ride' vocal part. Following Le Risque, Amby quoted I Love L.A. (Randy Newman).

Antarctica was dedicated to "all the polar bears in denial" and contained Daily Blues quotes and Ice V and Block of Ice (Osees) teases. Ice V contained Head On/Pill and Blindness (The Fall) teases. Gamma Knife contained Converge teases.  People-Vultures contained Iron Lung teases & quotes and Phantom Island quotes. Stu said "Free Palestine" before Boogieman Sam, which contained an Eternal Return vocal jam, Am I In Heaven? teases and a Riff Raff (AC/DC) tease. Slow Jam 1 contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Am I In Heaven? was unfinished and contained a Sad Pilot jam and Riff Raff (AC/DC) teases. The intro to Self-Immolate contained Am I In Heaven? teases and a drum solo where Stu, Joey, and an audience member shaved most of Stu's head.

Am I In Heaven? contained Antarctica and Hypertension teases. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo. Dragon featured a fan named Ignas on Stu’s guitar instead of Stu. After Dragon, Joey wished Stu a happy Pink Soup Day (a local festival in Vilnius about beet soup). Billabong Valley contained a See Me quote. Stu said "Fuck Putin" during Pleura. Le Risque was introduced as being called "Pink Soup", to which the band started chanting "Pink Soup", and Joey vocally teased Kernkraft 400 (Zombie Nation). The song itself featured a fan dressed as Evel Knievel on stage during Ambrose's verse, who Stu thanked after the song. Down The Sink was played for the first time since 2023-08-30 (76 show gap), in a new alternate synthpop arrangement, and contained Gilgamesh quotes. As Gilgamesh ended, Joey compared the band's synth playing at the end of the jam to Rammstein. Joey and Cavs teased Blind (Korn) before Trapdoor. The Dripping Tap featured Stu telling a story about him and Joey getting pink soup and how it was the best thing they had ever eaten, with Joey playing his guitar with his teeth because he "spilled pink soup on it", and contained a Tool jam featuring elements and variations of Forty Six & 2 and Schism with Motor Spirit quotes. After The Dripping Tap, Joey said "Free Palestine," "Glory to Ukraine" (from a sign in the audience) and "humanity."

data.jamchart_notes: Playful “Am I in Brisbane?” lyric changes and inspired jamming highlight this lengthy version. The band quietly build the song as they trickle teases in its calm intro before launching into the song proper. An extended section of mellow space unravels out of a dense, frenetic jam that sees some of the band’s freest playing all year before the song’s final verses kick off more high energy jamming with rapid-fire teases.
data.shownotes: The show was preceded by a welcome to country by Lafe Charlton. The intro to Nuclear Fusion was done by a fan named Keira. Following K.G.L.W. (Outro), Stu shouted out Jackson and Ducky from the stream team, and then said he wishes he was Ducky, then the band said he was Dougie from Twin Peaks. Am I In Heaven? had lyrics changed to "Am I In Brisbane?" and Inner Cell, The Dripping Tap, Head On/Pill, and Sad Pilot teases. Before Inner Cell, the band invited an audience member to do backflips on stage whenever he wanted, and he came up during the song. Inner Cell had lyrics changed to reference the backflip guy, and the song was stopped midway through because the band couldn't stop laughing at him. Before Predator X, which had a lyric changed to "Redditor X", the band shouted out Jason Galea. Following the song, the band sung the backwards man song from Freddy Got Fingered, but changed to the backflip man, and Joey teased Sultans of Swing (Dire Straits). Antarctica contained Hot Water teases. Before Hog Calling Contest, the band brought back the backflip guy as well as sound engineer Joe Santarpia to do pig noises. Gamma Knife contained Motor Spirit quotes.
